    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="452"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Marseille</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 13, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 12th, 4 p.m. Endeavor ascertain whether 15 men enter Spain after
                    release.</p>
                <p>Department desires return passports to Consulate for disposition as set forth
                    Department’s 162 April 7 to Embassy. Furnish details Embassy so matter can be
                    taken up with Minister Justice.</p>
                <p>Department does not desire that representative be sent for scheduled trials
                    Perpignan. However, keep in touch with cases and advise Department
                    developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
